addCandidate(string,string).details: Add a new candidate to the election. Can only be called before voting has started.
addCandidate(string,string).return: The ID of the newly added candidate.

checkVote().details: Checks if the current message sender has already voted.
checkVote().return: A boolean indicating the voting status.

getCandidate(uint256).details: Retrieves details for a specific candidate.
getCandidate(uint256).return: The candidate's ID, name, party, and vote count.

getCountCandidates().details: Gets the total number of registered candidates.

getDates().details: Retrieves the start and end dates of the voting period.
getDates().return: The start and end UNIX timestamps.

setDates(uint256,uint256).details: Set the start and end dates for the voting period. Can only be set once. Start date must be in the future. End date must be after start date.

params._endDate: The UNIX timestamp for the end of voting.
params._startDate: The UNIX timestamp for the start of voting.

vote(uint256).details: Allows a registered voter to cast their vote.

params._candidateID: The ID of the candidate to vote for.
